y approach to Krzysztof Kieślowski's Decalogue, a ten-film cycle of modern tales that touch on the ethical dilemmas of the Ten Commandments. The cycle's deft handling of moral ambiguity and inventive technique established Kieślowski as a major international director.Kieślowski once said, "Both the deep believer and the habitual skeptic experience toothaches in exactly the same way." Of Elephants and Toothaches takes seriously the range of thought, from theological to skeptical, condensed in the cycle's quite human tales. Bringing together scholars of film, philosophy, literature, and several religions, the volume ranges from individual responsibility, to religion in modernity, to familial bonds, to human desire and material greed. It explores Kieślowski's cycle as it relentlessly solicits an ethical response that stimulates both inner disquiet and interpersonal dialogue.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aReligion on television. 0aTelevision programsxMoral and ethical aspectszPoland. 4aBiblical intertext. 4aDecalogue. 4aEmbodied experience. 4aKrzysztof Kieslowski. 4adialogue. 4aethics in film. 4afilm cycle. 4amoral unrest. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aBadowska, Eva, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aParmeggiani, Francesca, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP / FUP eBook-Package 2016z978311071186840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823267125zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823267125423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780823267125.jpg  a978-3-11-071186-8  NYUP / FUP eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSH